If "Masquerade" custom nodes are installed, all this can be replaced by the single node "Unary Image Op" in "average" mode.
You should see a naked body here. If you see a gray mask instead, it's a bug. Change "ToBinaryMask" node's treshold to force "VAE Encode (for inpainting)" node to recalculate.
If it's problematic to get proper body mask, set the seed to "fixed" and choose or paint the best mask.
Currently unused, because inpainting clothes without surroundings wasn't seen successfull.

You can draw mask manually instead of relying on detectors (optional):
1) Open image in SAM Editor (right click on the node)
2) Mask clothes
3) Open image in Mask Editor
4) Improve the mask

nodes.title: How to
widgets_values:
1. Load picture.
2. Select a model.
3. Write prompt for naked body (very important, determines gender)
4. Write prompt for the whole picture (barely important)
5. Run it

If results are not good enough:
- select the best mask for clothes, or draw one manually
- select to not exclude hair, face or hands from the mask, if you want it redrawn
- select another skin color
- check your prompts
- fine tune KSampler nodes (purple)
If background is changing too much, and seams are not really a problem, decrease denoise here.
If outline of an old clothes is still visible, there is no other choise but to siginificantly increase denoise here.

If you get patches of skin around face, decrease treshold.
If you get patches of clothes under hair, increase treshold.
